description: This Java class 'JobStatusResponse' serves as a Data Transfer Object (DTO) for conveying the status and related information of a finetuning job in the backend API. It includes fields such as job ID, model name, status, dataset ID, URLs or paths for logs, metrics, artifacts, error messages, and timestamps for creation and update.

classes.name: JobStatusResponse
classes.description: A DTO class representing the current status and metadata of a finetuning job.

methods.name: getId
methods.description: Returns the job ID.

methods.name: getModelName
methods.description: Returns the name of the model.

methods.name: getStatus
methods.description: Returns the current status of the finetuning job.

methods.name: getDatasetId
methods.description: Returns the dataset ID associated with the job.

methods.name: getLogsPath
methods.description: Returns the URL or path to the logs.

methods.name: getMetricsPath
methods.description: Returns the URL or path to the metrics.

methods.name: getArtifactPath
methods.description: Returns the URL or path to the artifact if the job succeeded.

methods.name: getErrorMessage
methods.description: Returns the error message if the job failed.

methods.name: getCreatedAt
methods.description: Returns the timestamp when the job was created.

methods.name: getUpdatedAt
methods.description: Returns the timestamp when the job was last updated.

methods.name: setId
methods.description: Sets the job ID.

methods.name: setModelName
methods.description: Sets the model name.

methods.name: setStatus
methods.description: Sets the status of the job.

methods.name: setDatasetId
methods.description: Sets the dataset ID.

methods.name: setLogsPath
methods.description: Sets the logs URL or path.

methods.name: setMetricsPath
methods.description: Sets the metrics URL or path.

methods.name: setArtifactPath
methods.description: Sets the artifact URL or path.

methods.name: setErrorMessage
methods.description: Sets the error message.

methods.name: setCreatedAt
methods.description: Sets the creation timestamp.

methods.name: setUpdatedAt
methods.description: Sets the last update timestamp.
